Low blood pressure, also called hypotension, is when your blood pressure lowers down and causes inadequacy of the blood flow to the body organs as well as manifesting with symptoms such as light headedness, dizziness, and even fainting. Also a reading which is less than 90/60mmHg is termed as low blood pressure. Hypotension has many possible causes from lifestyle choices, to medication or an underlying health condition. It is normal for your blood pressures to vary throughout the day depending on the activities that you are doing. Furthermore, blood pressure depends on the surrounding environment and temperature. In hot weather, people tend to exhibit low blood pressure. Similarly what and when you have eaten could all affect your blood pressure readings. If your blood pressure is still considered low after taking these factors into account, other causes are as follows;